Class MEProcessData

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractTreeNode
      • org.sbml.jsbml.xml.XMLToken
        • org.sbml.jsbml.xml.XMLNode
          • sbmlme.MEAbstractXMLNodePlugin
            • sbmlme.MEProcessData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, org.sbml.jsbml.util.TreeNodeWithChangeSupport, MEConstants

    public class MEProcessData
extends MEAbstractXMLNodePlugin
implements MEConstants
    Implements methods for creating ProcessData objects for the annotation of the SBML model. These objects contain data which is used in COBRAme in several different reactions and is stored in its own objects to reduce redundancy.

    In SBMLme only StoichiometricData, TranslocationData and SubreactionData are stored in the MEProcessData. The other ProcessData objects from COBRAme are directly added to the annotations of the specific reactions since they are in a 1:1 relation with the reactions.

    Author:
    Marc A. Voigt

      • addSubreactionData

        public void addSubreactionData(MEProcessData processData,
                               java.lang.String id,
                               double keff,
                               java.util.List<java.lang.String> enzymeReferences,
                               java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> elementContributions,
                               java.util.List<java.lang.String> speciesReferences,
                               java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> stoichiometries)
        Create and add a new SubreactionData object to the list of SubreactionData.

        For correct function the given MEProcessData object needs to have the list of SubreactionData as its first child.

        Parameters:
        processData - the MEProcessData object that the subreaction should be added to
        id - the id of the new subreaction
        keff - the effective turnover rate of enzymes in the subreaction
        enzymeReferences - list with references to enzymes used in the subreaction, may be null
        elementContributions - map with elements and their net contributions to a macromolecule by the subreaction, may be null
        speciesReferences - list with ids of species used in the subreaction process
        stoichiometries - list with stoichiometries of species in the subreaction

      • addTranslocationData

        public void addTranslocationData(MEProcessData processData,
                                 java.lang.String id,
                                 double keff,
                                 java.util.List<java.lang.String> enzymeReferences,
                                 java.util.List<java.lang.Boolean> fixedKeff,
                                 java.util.List<java.lang.Boolean> listLengthDependent,
                                 java.util.List<java.lang.String> speciesReferences,
                                 java.util.List<java.lang.Double> stoichiometries,
                                 boolean lengthDependentEnergy)
        Create and add a new SubreactionData object to the list of TranslocationData.

        For correct function the given MEProcessData object needs to have the list of TranslocationData as its second child.

        Parameters:
        processData - the MEProcessData object that the translocation should be added to
        id - the id of the new translocation
        keff - the effective turnover rate of enzymes in the translocation
        enzymeReferences - list with the ids of enzymes used in the translocation
        fixedKeff - list with information whether an enzyme coupling has a fixed keff in the translocation process
        listLengthDependent - list with information whether the enzyme coupling is length dependent in the translocation process
        speciesReferences - list with ids of species used in the translocation process
        stoichiometries - list with stoichiometries of species in the translocation process
        lengthDependentEnergy - whether the ATP cost of the translocation is dependent on the length of the protein

      • addStoichiometricData

        public void addStoichiometricData(MEProcessData processData,
                                  java.lang.String id,
                                  java.lang.Double lowerFluxBound,
                                  java.lang.Double upperFluxBound,
                                  java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Double> subreactionMap,
                                  java.util.List<java.lang.String> speciesReferences,
                                  java.util.List<java.lang.Double> stoichiometries)
        Create and add a new StoichiometricData object to the list of StoichiometricData.

        For correct function the given MEProcessData object needs to have the list of StoichiometricData as its third child.

        Parameters:
        processData - the MEProcessData object that the StoichiometricData object should be added to
        id - the id of the new StoichiometricData object
        lowerFluxBound - the lower flux bound of the metabolic reaction
        upperFluxBound - the upper flux bound of the metabolic reaction
        subreactionMap - the map with the ids and coefficients of the subreactions that take part in the reaction, may be null
        speciesReferences - list with ids of species used in the metabolic reaction
        stoichiometries - list with stoichiometries of species in the metabolic reaction
